control (glucose homeostasis, cognitive function, frailty phenotype, gut 
microbiota profile, immune parameters), while others remained unvariable.
CONCLUSIONS: The use of probiotics and prebiotics raises a great opportunity to 
modulate the process of aging and looks promising for health prevention in old 
adults. However, more RCTs in subjects older than 65 years are needed to 
elucidate the suitability of these supplementations and establish the underlying 
potential mechanisms.

